<1ST_LINE>r a PM-GarciaArraignment     12-02 0283</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Garcia Arraignment,0292</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bronx Congressman, Wife Plead Innocent to Wedtech Charges</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN M. DOYLE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   For the second time in two years, a Bronx
congressman is proclaiming his innocence in the Wedtech corruption
scandal.
   U.S. Rep. Robert Garcia and his wife, Jane Lee Garcia, pleaded
innocent Thursday to charges they participated in a bribery and
extortion scheme involving Wedtech Corp., a defunct defense
contractor.
   ``I'm innocent and when the moment comes I'll be exonerated,''
Garcia told reporters as the couple entered the courthouse.
   Following their arraignment before a federal magistrate, the
55-year-old Bronx Democrat and his 48-year-old wife were released
without bail.
   U.S. District Judge Leonard B. Sand set a tentative trial date of
June 1, and scheduled a preliminary hearing for Jan. 3.
   The Garcias and a lawyer from Puerto Rico, Ralph Vallone Jr., 41,
were indicted last week in an alleged conspiracy to obtain $185,000
in cash, interest-free loans and jewelry from Wedtech.
   The indictment came just a few days after former U.S. Rep. Mario
Biaggi, another Bronx Democrat, and four others were sentenced to
prison for their conviction in a Wedtech-related racketeering trial.
   Wedtech grew from a small machine shop into a multimillion-dollar
business through a series of no-bid government contracts obtained
through a federal minority business program.
   Federal and state investigations uncovered a web of corruption
involving Wedtech payoffs extending from the Bronx to Washington.
   The seven-count indictment accused Garcia of using his official
position to demand and obtain payoffs from Wedtech, which was
headquartered in his congressional district.
   Garcia, a congressman since 1978, is charged with extortion,
conspiracy, bribery and receipt of illegal gratuities. His wife, 48,
faces similar charges.
</TEXT>
