<HEAD>Father Who Stabbed Heroin Addict Son Acquitted</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIVERPOOL, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who stabbed his heroin-addict son
to death was acquitted of murder and manslaughter Friday.
   A jury took 40 minutes to find John Albertina innocent in the
killing of his 21-year-old son, Stephen, on March 11.
   Albertina, 51, hugged weeping family members at the end of the
three-day trial.
   He told the court he acted in self-defense after his son came at
him with a wrench during a family fight.
   Since becoming a heroin addict, the youth sometimes attacked his
family. He broke a sister's jaw, broke another sister's fingers and
was arrested for threatening to kill them, the court heard.
   On the night of his death, he flew into a rage after his father
told him, ``I don't hate you, I despise you.'' The young man was
stabbed as he and his father wrestled.
