<HEAD>Explosion Shatters Windows at Atomic Weapons Center</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BURGHFIELD, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A controlled explosion at a government
atomic weapons factory shattered windows Friday, but there were no
injuries, the Ministry of Defense said.
   The blast at the Atomic Weapons Establishment in an area set
aside for destroying conventional explosives occurred with more
force than expected, a defense spokeswoman saidy.
   Martin O'Neill, the opposition Labor Party spokesman on defense
matters, called for an inquiry at the site, 40 miles southwest of
London.
   ``The veil of secrecy which surrounds activities at
establishments like Burghfield has to be lifted when the public and
the surrounding area have been disturbed and shocked by an explosion
such as this,'' he said.
   Bruce Kent of the Campaign for Nuclear Disarmament said ``it is
incredible that conventional explosives should be destroyed by
burning in the middle of a nuclear bomb factory.''
