<HEAD>Real Estate Mogul To Be Tour Guide For Gorbachev</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Multimillionaire developer Donald Trump will play
tour guide during Soviet President Mikhail Gorbachev's visit to
Trump's upscale retail mall next week, a Trump spokesman said Friday.
   Gorbachev and his wife, Raisa, who will be in New York to meet
President Reagan and President-elect George Bush, are expected to
spend about a half-hour Thursday inside the marble-lined shopping
atrium on Fifth Avenue, said Trump spokesman Dan Klores.
   Due to security reasons, they may only get to browse through
stores on the first of the mall's six levels.
   But with stores like Cartier jewelers, Charles Jourdan shoes and
a Bonwit Teller department store, Gorbachev should come away with a
representative feeling of what upscale means.
   A large entourage of Soviet and U.S. security personnel and
reporters will join the tour.
   Trump, who lives on the top three floors of the 68-floor Trump
Tower, originally wanted to show the Soviet leader a large indoor
swimming pool in one of the top-priced tower apartments. But Klores
said that idea was scrapped because of time and security
restrictions.
   The meeting between the Soviet leader and one of America's
leading capitalists was arranged after Trump sent a letter to the
Soviet Embassy inviting Gorbachev to visit Trump Tower and the Plaza
Hotel, a recent Trump acquisition.
   Klores said Trump met Gorbachev at a White House dinner during
the Soviet leader's last visit to the United States. ``They spoke
and they got along, so when he knew Gorbachev was coming, he (Trump)
wrote him a note,'' Klores said.
   ``On Wednesday, the Soviets responded and said they'd be
delighted to come.''
