<HEAD>Dollar Unchanged, Share Prices Drop</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar remained unchanged against the Japanese
yen today, while share prices fell back slightly.
   The dollar closed at 121.64 yen, the same as its opening. The
currency, which started the day's trading 0.07 yen higher than
Thursday's close of 121.57, moved in a narrow range of 121.60-121.68
yen.
   ``It ranged in a narrow range throughout the day.... There were
few moves to take fresh dollar positions prior to the release of the
U.S. unemployment rate,'' said a dealer with the Bank of Tokyo.
   The U.S. Labor Department was scheduled to announce its latest
monthly jobless figures for November later today.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, a 37.44-point loser the previous day, shed 9.21
points, or 0.03 percent, to finish trading at 29,532.25. The index
gained 26.19 points during the morning session, but edged down in
the afternoon.
