<1ST_LINE>r f PM-Recall-ToyTrain     12-02 0187</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Recall-Toy Train,0194</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Electric Toy Train Recalled</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The ``Talking Silver Rail Express'' toy train
is being recalled because of a potential fire hazard, according to
the Consumer Product Safety Commission.
   The importer, New Bright Industries of Canton, Mich., had
received 16 reports of the toys short circuiting and causing the
tender car to overheat, with nine cases in which the train caught
fire, the agency said. No injuries have been reported.
   Involved in the recall are about 38,000 of the toy trains with
metal plug connectors between the tender car and the locomotive
section. They were manufactured in Hong Kong in 1986 and were
identified as Model 1170.
   Newer train sets carrying that model number, but having a plastic
plug connector between the two cars, are not involved in the recall,
the commission said.
   Owners of the recalled train sets can obtain a free replacement
by calling New Bright Industries at 1-800-325-5630. Michigan
residents should call collect at 1-313-981-0020. Consumers can also
write to New Bright Industries, 41911 Ford Road, Canton, Mich.,
48187.
   Those needing more information can contact the commission at
1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
