<HEAD>Grain Futures Open Lower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Futures prices of grain and soybeans opened
slightly lower today on the Chicago Board of Trade in a continuation
of the sell-off that ended Thursday's trading session.
   Analysts said the early decline did not appear to be linked to
any bearish new supply-and-demand developments.
   In fact, reports of new shipments of South American soybean meal
