<HEAD>London Stocks Lower</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New throughout.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stocks fell Friday, reflecting what analysts called
deepened worries about the outlook for British economic growth and
corporate profits after recent rises in interest rates.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 13.7
points, or 0.8 percent, to 1,765.0. Volume on the London Stock
Exchange was moderate, with 486.3 million shares changing hands,
compared with 467.1 million shares Thursday.
